  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Released in 2026 by Peter Sheridan Dodds at the University of Vermont, this dataset provides essential meaning word scores underpinning the ousiometric GPADS framework \u2014 a multidimensional semantic space encompassing Goodness, Power, Aggression, Danger, and Structure. Though freshly published, it has already attracted 123 views and 32 downloads on Zenodo, and has been picked up in at least one downstream research context indexed by Europe PMC, signalling early adoption within the computational linguistics and natural language processing communities.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The dataset sits at the intersection of linguistics, natural language processing, and quantitative psychology, offering word-level scores calibrated to five conceptually distinct semantic dimensions. The GPADS framework extends earlier work on affective meaning \u2014 most notably valence-based approaches \u2014 by disaggregating meaning into components that capture not only evaluative sentiment (Goodness) but also social and physical force-related dimensions (Power, Aggression, Danger) and organizational properties (Structure). Such granularity is increasingly sought in computational text analysis, where blunt sentiment scores often fail to distinguish, say, authoritative language from threatening language. The conceptual vocabulary tagged in OpenAlex \u2014 spanning group theory, existential meaning, and natural language processing \u2014 reflects the genuinely cross-disciplinary ambition of the resource.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Stewardship of the dataset follows sound open-science practice. It is hosted on Zenodo, a CERN-operated repository registered in re3data and carrying DOI-based persistent identifiers, with open access ensured under a green open-access designation. Two versioned releases are formally registered as related identifiers, meaning the scholarly record can track provenance across updates \u2014 a detail that matters when downstream studies rely on specific score distributions. The availability of multiple versions also allows researchers to assess the stability of word scores as the underlying methodology is refined.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Early usage indicators, while modest, are consistent with a dataset at the very start of its citation lifecycle. The 32 downloads recorded against 123 views suggests a conversion rate that indicates genuine interest rather than casual browsing, and the confirmed mention in a Europe PMC-indexed article points to uptake in biomedical or health-adjacent text-analysis research \u2014 a domain where distinguishing danger-coded from aggression-coded language, for example, carries practical significance. A marginal alignment with the Sustainable Development Goal of Reduced Inequalities has also been flagged, plausibly reflecting the broader potential of nuanced semantic tools for studying power dynamics and social disparities in large text corpora.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, this resource represents a carefully structured lexical instrument from an established researcher in computational social science. Its value will ultimately be demonstrated through uptake in peer-reviewed studies that apply or benchmark the GPADS dimensions, and the initial signals \u2014 early downloads, a versioned release chain, and an indexed downstream mention \u2014 suggest the community is beginning to engage with it in exactly that spirit.</p>",
